@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Maruti Swift vs Hyundai Grand i10 Nios: 2025 Hatchback Comparison";
}
@section MetaTags {
    <meta name="keywords" content="Maruti Swift vs Hyundai Grand i10 Nios, Swift vs i10 Nios comparison 2025, Swift mileage 2025, i10 Nios features 2025, Best hatchback in India 2025, Swift vs i10 Nios NVH comparison, Hyundai i10 Nios review, Maruti Swift specifications, Hyundai Grand i10 Nios specifications, Swift vs i10 Nios which is better, Hatchback comparison India 2025, Maruti vs Hyundai review, Affordable cars in India 2025, Best car for city commute 2025" />
    <meta name="description" content="Compare Maruti Swift vs Hyundai Grand i10 Nios in 2025. Check NVH levels, features, performance, price, and decide which hatchback is best for your needs" />
}

@functions {
    public string Truncate(string input, int length)
    {
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(input) || input.Length <= length)
            return input;
        return input.Substring(0, length) + "...";
    }
}
<body id="bg">
    @* <div class="header-img"><img src="~/images/main-slider/header.png" alt="bikecarhubheaderimage" title="bikecarhubheaderimage" /></div> *@
    <div class="m-t90">
        <div><h1 class="latest-bike-head">@Model.BlogHeading</h1></div>
        <div class=" latest-bike-container">
            @* <div style="background-image:url(@ViewBag.TWNews.ImageURL);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position: center;background-size:contain ;height: 400px;box-shadow: 5px 10px 8px #888888;border-radius:10px;background-color:#ebecee;padding:60px;"></div> *@
            <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-image">
                <img src="@Model.ImageURL" alt="@Model.BlogHeading" title="@Model.BlogHeading" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='@Url.Content("~/images/default.jpg")';" />
                <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-text">
                    <p><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> @Model.Date?.ToString("d MMM yyyy")</p>
                    @* <p>@ViewBag.TWNews.NewsSummary</p> *@
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Written by:</span> BikeCarHub Editorial Team</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Published on:</span> 1th July 2025</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Introduction</h2>

                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <p>In this detailed comparison by <span class="font-weight-700"><a class="for-link" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">BikeCarHub</a></span>, we will break down every important aspect like NVH, performance, features, pricing, and more to help you decide which hatchback suits you best in 2025.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Engine Layout & NVH</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Swift</h3>
             
                <ul>
                    <li>Powered by a <strong>1.2L, 3-cylinder Z-series petrol engine</strong> producing ~82hp and ~112Nm torque</li>
                    <li>Available with mild-hybrid technology</li>
                    <li>Three-cylinder engines inherently produce more vibration than four-cylinders</li>
                    <li>Some owners note noticeable cabin resonance and tinny panel noise</li>
                </ul>
                <p>"The resonance from the body panels make me uncomfortable"</p>
                <p>Swift benefits from modest NVH improvements in the facelift, but budget plastics and lighter build mean some cabin harshness remains.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Grand i10 Nios</h3>
               
                <ul>
                    <li>Uses a <strong>1.2L, 4-cylinder Kappa petrol engine</strong> (~83hp, 114Nm torque)</li>
                    <li>Also offered in CNG variant</li>
                    <li>Four-cylinder design ensures smoother, quieter operation</li>
                    <li>Hyundai strengthened the platform and increased sound-deadening</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Owner retrospectives frequently praise its refined comfort and low NVH.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> i10 Nios clearly outperforms Swift in NVH with its smoother engine and better insulation.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Ride Quality & Handling</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Swift</h3>
                <p>Sporty tuning offers agile, fun-to-drive dynamics. Turbo mild-hybrid aside, its ride can feel firm, with more transmitted road feedback—pleasing to enthusiasts but less isolating on poor tarmac.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Grand i10 Nios</h3>
                <p>Tuned for comfort, the re-engineered suspension smooths bumps better and maintains composure on uneven roads. NVH gains further elevate its refinement.</p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Swift for sporty handling, i10 Nios for comfort.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Features & Safety Comparison</h2>
                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="comparison-table-content">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th class="text-center">Feature</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Maruti Swift</th>
                                <th class="text-center">Hyundai Grand i10 Nios</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Infotainment</td>
                                <td>7-9" touchscreen, wireless Android Auto/Apple CarPlay</td>
                                <td>8" touchscreen, wireless charger, voice commands</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Climate & Convenience</td>
                                <td>Rear AC vents, cruise, semi-digital cluster</td>
                                <td>Rear AC vents, cooled glove box, TPMS</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="compare-head-text">
                                <td>Safety</td>
                                <td>Up to 6 airbags, ABS+EBD, ESC, hill assist</td>
                                <td>Same plus tire-pressure monitoring</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Swift</span> has ramped up its features but still lacks TPMS and cooled glove-box. <span class="font-weight-700">Nios</span> counters with convenient touches enhancing daily usability.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Performance & Fuel Efficiency</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Swift:</span> Z-series petrol delivers ~24.8 kmpl (manual) and up to 25.8 kmpl (AMT). Mild-hybrid tech further improves economy.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Nios:</span> Delivers ~20.7-20.1 kmpl in petrol, with CNG option offering ~27.3 km/kg.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Swift leads in fuel efficiency, especially with hybrid. Nios' CNG is appealing but less refined.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Pricing & Value (India, Ex-Showroom)</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Swift:</span> ₹6.5 - 9.6 L approx</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Nios:</span> ₹5.9 - 8.6 L approx</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Swift costs more but offers superior fuel economy and sporty dynamics. Nios remains budget-friendly with added comforts.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">NVH: The Final Verdict</h2>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Hyundai Grand i10 Nios</span> clearly outperforms <span class="font-weight-700">Swift</span> in NVH. A smoother four-cylinder engine, enhanced insulation, and chassis refinement yield a serene cabin, especially on highways and poor roads. While Swift's charm lies in its lively driving and mileage, it can feel noisier—owners note tinny panels, engine buzz, and overall cabin resonance.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Pros and Cons</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Maruti Swift</h3>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Pros:</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Top-tier fuel efficiency (especially mild-hybrid)</li>
                    <li>Sportier driving and sharper styling</li>
                    <li>Lower-priced entry point</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Cons:</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Noticeable cabin noise and vibration</li>
                    <li>Firmer ride quality</li>
                    <li>Lacks some convenience features</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Hyundai Grand i10 Nios</h3>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Pros:</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Superior NVH and refinement</li>
                    <li>Comfort-focused ride quality</li>
                    <li>Convenience features (TPMS, cooled glovebox)</li>
                    <li>More affordable pricing</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Cons:</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Lower fuel efficiency in petrol variant</li>
                    <li>Less engaging to drive</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Which One Should You Buy?</h2>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Choose Maruti Swift (2025) if you want:</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Top-tier fuel efficiency (especially mild-hybrid)</li>
                    <li>Sportier driving and sharper styling</li>
                    <li>Lower-priced entry point</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Pick Hyundai Grand i10 Nios if you prefer:</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Smoother, quieter cabin and refined NVH</li>
                    <li>Comfort-focused ride with daily usability</li>
                    <li>Convenience features (TPMS, cooled glovebox) at a lower cost</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Final Verdict:</span></p>
                <p>The <strong>Swift</strong> wins the numbers game with efficiency and driving fun; the <strong>Grand i10 Nios</strong> takes the crown in NVH refinement and everyday comfort. Whichever you choose, you're opting for a dependable Indian hatchback—but understanding their core personalities ensures you'll pick the one that aligns with your driving style and comfort preferences.</p>

